body_html:
I had an offline discussion with @dr4b and @av8ramit - thanks for your help!

Here's what happened. By default (without choosing an explicit version), the tensorflow.org site shows the docs for the most recent released version. Right now that's v1.4, which was released in early November. The doc fixes were merged on 11/28, so they didn't make it into v1.4, and thus the default docs are still broken.

cddf8d8 was just merged, which patched the doc fixes into v1.4. Now we just need to regenerate the docs and the site will be fixed.

I'll leave this open until the site is really fixed.

I had an offline discussion with @dr4b and @av8ramit - thanks for your help!

Here's what happened.  By default (without choosing an explicit version), the tensorflow.org site shows the docs for the most recent released version.  Right now that's v1.4, which was released in early November.  The doc fixes were merged on 11/28, so they didn't make it into v1.4, and thus the default docs are still broken.

cddf8d82dec9fff526f5c064add725b7f35f95fa was just merged, which patched the doc fixes into v1.4.  Now we just need to regenerate the docs and the site will be fixed.

I'll leave this open until the site is really fixed.
